Sentencas: La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta (LSCFN) was applied as both anode and cathode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) with zirconia based electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell with LSCFN electrode was fabricated by tape-casting and screen printing.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: Fabrication process was optimized firstly by comparing co-sintering and separate-sintering of electrode and electrolyte.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: To further improve the LSCFN electrode properties, oxygen ionic conductor of Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) was added into the LSCFN electrode.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: The preferred composition of LSCFN-GDC composite electrode was found to be 1: 1 in weight ratio with polarization resistance of 0.16 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of LSCFN-GDC parallel to GDC/YSZ/GDC parallel to LSCFN-GDC tested in H-2 and CH4 with 3% H2O were 395 mW cm(-2) and 124 mW cm(-2) at 850 degrees C, respectively, which were much higher than that of LSCFN parallel to GDC/YSZ/GDC
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: parallel to LSCFN cells at same condition, possibly due to the extension of the triple phase boundary induced by the addition of GDC.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte

Sentencas: The cell showed reasonable stability using H-2 and CH4 with 3% H2O as fuels and no significant power output degradation was observed after total 200 h operation.
Titulo: Fabrication and optimization of La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell with zirconia based electrolyte
